                "prefix": 3.2,
                "text": "Managing Director on behalf of Mid Essex Hospital Services NHS Trust"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 10,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 3.3,
                "text": "Imaging Services Manager"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 11,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 3.4,
                "text": "Diagnostics and Therapies Lead"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 12,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 3.5,
                "text": "Clinical Lead Radiologist"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 13,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 3.6,
                "text": "Referring Clinician"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 14,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 3.7,
                "text": "Advanced Practitioner Radiographer or Sonographer"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 15,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Appendix 1 Individual Reporting Agreement Template Appendix 2 Background"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 16,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Appendix 3 Equality Impact Assessment Form"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 17,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 1.1,
                "text": "To authorise appropriately qualified, registered radiographers and sonographers to provide clinical reports on imaging examinations."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 18,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 2.1,
                "text": "This policy covers appropriately qualified radiographic staff employed by Mid Essex Hospitals' Service NHS Trust to produce clinical reports for their defined speciality and according to their Individual Reporting Agreement (see 4)."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 19,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 2.2,
                "text": "The policy covers referrals from all sources including Emergency, Primary and Secondary Care settings inclusive of General Practitioners and authorised non- medical practitioners."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 20,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 2.3,
                "text": "The reporting radiographer/sonographer will evaluate radiology images in order to provide a clinical report to include:"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 21,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Clinical details;"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 22,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Technical quality of the imaging;"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 23,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Use and dose of contrast agent / radioisotope, where appropriate;"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 24,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Description of image appearances ;"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 25,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "A conclusion or interpretation of the findings in the clinical context, including any differential diagnoses where appropriate;"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 26,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Recommendations for further imaging if appropriate;"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 27,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Reference to a Consultant Radiologist, including their details, if their opinion has been sought with regards to image appearances or further imaging."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 28,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 2.4,
                "text": "Requests for an opinion on examinations which fall outside the radiographer or sonographer's knowledge will be passed on to a Radiologist."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 29,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 2.5,
                "text": "Radiographers may decline to report on any examinations that they consider to be beyond their current level of expertise. These examinations will remain on the unallocated worklist on CRIS for plain film or to an identified Radiologist's work list (as defined in the Individual Reporting Agreement) for other modalities."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 30,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 2.6,
                "text": "Specific exclusions may be included in the Individual Reporting Agreements (see 4)."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 31,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 3.1,
                "text": "All Parties"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 32,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "3.1.1 All parties must be certain that the member of staff is suitably qualified, experienced and competent to carry out the responsibilities delegated to them. In addition, the following roles and responsibilities apply."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 33,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "3.1.2 Staff will be supported to develop their role through the Trusts clinical governance and continuing professional development arrangements."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 34,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 3.2,
                "text": "Managing Director"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 35,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "3.2.1  To be accountable for ensuring appropriate policies are in place, with day to day responsibility delegated to the Imaging Services Manager."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 36,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 3.3,
                "text": "Imaging Services Manager"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 37,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "3.3.1 To maintain a central list of authorised Advanced Practitioner Radiographers and Sonographers."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 38,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "3.3.2 To approve the delegation of reporting agreements."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 39,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "3.3.3 To ensure authors undertake a regular review of this policy."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 40,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "3.3.4 To ensure appropriate training is available and competency requirements are met."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 41,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 3.4,
                "text": "Diagnostics & Therapies Lead"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 42,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "3.4.1  To be responsible for ensuring that this policy is implemented operationally and that governance processes are followed."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 43,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 3.5,
                "text": "Clinical Lead Radiologist"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 44,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "3.5.1  When delegating a role, the Clinical Lead Radiologist retains full clinical and managerial responsibility for the patient. The Clinical Lead Radiologist shares responsibility for proper performance of the task not only with the delegated member of staff but also that person's employer."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 45,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 3.6,
                "text": "Referring Clinician"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 46,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "3.6.1  The referrer remains responsible for acting upon any findings whether expected or not."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 47,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 3.7,
                "text": "Advanced Practitioner Radiographer or Sonographer"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 48,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "3.7.1  The Advanced Practitioner Radiographer or Sonographer must:-"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 49,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Hold a Society of Radiographers Accredited Post Graduate Qualification in Clinical Reporting or Local Training Agreement in the absence of SOR Accredited Courses;"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 50,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Complete an Individual Reporting Agreement, signed by the Imaging Services Manager and Clinical Lead Radiologist;"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 51,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Hold valid professional insurance to cover reporting activities (recommended to use Society of Radiographers);"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 52,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Maintain and demonstrate competence through regular audit and Continued Professional Development opportunities;"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 53,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Should maintain regular contact with a named Radiologist Mentor;"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 54,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Radiographers will adhere to RCR guidance and Trust procedures with regards to the communication of critical, urgent and unexpected significant radiological findings. Action taken will be documented in the report content;"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 55,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Radiographers will consult with a Radiologist if they feel the patient should be re- called for immediate further high dose imaging i.e. CT, MR, NM (as opposed to \u2018considering further imaging if clinically appropriate', detailed in the report content). The only exception to this when a lung cancer is strongly suspected for which referral to CT and the chest clinic can be made without consulting a radiologist;"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 56,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Retain responsibility for reports issued and verified under their name."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 57,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 4.0,
                "text": "Individual Reporting Agreements"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 58,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 1.0,
                "text": "This document can be found in Appendix"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 59,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 4.2,
                "text": "Each Advanced Practitioner Radiographer and Sonographer must have a completed Individual Reporting Agreement detailing the examinations in which they are qualified to report. This must be signed by the ISM, Radiology Clinical Lead and the individual before reporting activity is instigated."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 60,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 4.3,
                "text": "A master copy will be held by the Imaging Services Manager (ISM) and be available on the Radiology Department shared drive."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 61,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 5.0,
                "text": "Equality Impact Assessment"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 62,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 5.1,
                "text": "Mid Essex Hospital Services NHS Trust is committed to the provision of a service that is fair, accessible and meets the needs of all individuals. (Refer to Appendix 3)"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 63,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 6.0,
                "text": "Breaches"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 64,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 6.1,
                "text": "Advanced Practitioner Radiographers and Sonographers will adhere to the Standards of Professional Conduct as detailed by the Health Care Professions Council and Society and College of Radiographers."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 65,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 6.2,
                "text": "A DATIX web may be completed for any Advanced Practitioner Radiographer or Sonographer identified as working outside of their Individual Reporting Agreement."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 66,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 7.0,
                "text": "Audit and Monitoring"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 67,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 7.1,
                "text": "Any reporting discrepancies will be addressed initially to the original Reporter and Radiologist Mentor. They should be highlighted to the Lead Radiologist for Discrepancy Reporting."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 68,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 7.2,
                "text": "Regular documented audit of practice should be performed. This may take a variety of forms which may include self audit, peer review, case studies, formal test banks, radiologist mentoring and discrepancy / MDT meetings. Evidence of audit activity should form part of the Continual Professional Development portfolio as part of the requirement for Health and Care Professions Council registration."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 69,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 7.3,
                "text": "Identified reporting performance issues should be addressed by re-education, radiologist support and re-audit to ensure competency is maintained."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 70,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 8.1,
                "text": "Governance will upload the policy to the intranet and website after ratification. It is the responsibility of the author to notify key staff individually by e-mail."
